# JavaScript and the Asset Boundary

## One Stack Per App

Rails 7+ defaults to **importmap** for JavaScript and **Propshaft** for static assets — no Node required for Hello World. If you add **jsbundling-rails**, **cssbundling-rails**, or **Vite**, commit to **one** delivery story. Do not run importmap pins and a separate bundled “app shell” that both load Turbo — pick a path and document it.

Canonical detail: **`skills/writing-javascript/references/patterns.md`**. Turbo, frames, streams, Stimulus *behaviour*: **`skills/writing-hotwire/references/patterns.md`**, **`rules/hotwire.mdc`**. Tailwind and global CSS: **`rules/css-tailwind.mdc`**, **`skills/writing-css-tailwind/references/patterns.md`** — not the JS boundary.

## Where JavaScript Lives

- **Entry** — `app/javascript/application.js` imports Stimulus and any pinned modules.
- **Stimulus** — `app/javascript/controllers/**/*_controller.js`, registered from the application entry (e.g. `eagerLoadControllersFrom("controllers")` with importmap).
- **Layouts** — `javascript_importmap_tags` (importmap) or the helper your bundler documents — not ad hoc `<script src="https://cdn…">` for app logic.

## Boundary Rules

- **HTML + Turbo** own navigation and server-backed state for first-party pages.
- **Stimulus** enhances the DOM; it does not replace routes, sessions, or authorization.
- **No parallel client router** or JSON-first CRUD for pages you already render with ERB — that fights the asset pipeline *and* Hotwire.

## Anti-Patterns

| Anti-Pattern | Instead |
|-------------|---------|
| Two competing JS pipelines (importmap + heavy webpack for same app chrome) | One strategy; simplify |
| `fetch` + JSON for every mutation on same-origin pages you control | Forms, Turbo, streams |
| Client-only source of truth for domain state | Server session + HTML |
| Stimulus controllers importing a full “app store” | Small controllers; server truth |

## Out of Scope

React/Vue/Svelte as the primary shell, micro-frontends, and CDN-only frontends decoupled from Rails — not this rule. Propshaft vs Sprockets migration nuance: **`skills/writing-javascript/references/patterns.md`**.
